name: language_html_data_attribute_unquoted_space_breakout
description: |
  In an unquoted attribute value, ASCII space ends the value and the remaining
  bytes create a harmless data-xss-canary attribute. Quoted attributes or DOM
  property assignment preserve the complete string as data.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "html-attribute-context"
  - "unquoted-attribute"
  - "whitespace"
  - "attribute-injection"
  - "inert-canary"
---
x data-xss-canary=y
